{ This is a very dangerous trap in the English against the Dutch. I've learned that this is lost the hard way. }
1. c4 f5 2. g3 Nf6 3. Bg2 g6 4. Nc3 Bg7 5. d3 O-O 6. e4 d6 7. Nge2 Nc6 8. O-O e5 9. h3? { A seemingly innocent move. Prepared Be3 or f4 next move. It is even the most popular 9th move! But it actually loses due to Black's next reply: } 9... f4! { And now White is very cramped. It is a pawn sacrifice, but White's position is already tangled, and the h3 pawn only adds to the list of weaknesses. Black gets quick development in the attack } 10. gxf4 Nh5 11. fxe5 dxe5 12. f4 Qh4 { h3 is soon to be lost, and Black's pieces are all coming in. } *


